{"questionId":"9067118","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Aspartame is a derivative of a dipeptide formed between two amino acids, phenylalanine (Phe) and aspartic acid (Asp).</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Draw a circle around the functional group formed between the amino acids and state its name.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/91972b7aceeef4c07b9c67d3519e12076004c042.png\" width=\"327\" height=\"171\"></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Name:&nbsp;</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"__IMG__/ad5e7c39c75c661ee1228d313af870b0c1f3a893.png\" width=\"322\" height=\"178\"></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><em>Name</em>:<br>amide/amido/carboxamide&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;Accept “peptide bond/linkage”.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9067118","referenceCode":"19M.3.sl.TZ1.8a","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Draw a circle around the functional group formed between the amino acids and state its name. Name:","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Options","Options","B: Biochemistry","B.2 Proteins and enzymes","Options","B: Biochemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}